Andromeda is an advance of Quantum Dynamics technologies, i.e. Sums of Products, 
into an area of electronic structure using the Gaussian-Sinc method for development of
interactions.  




Added commands to build runtime in each species subdirectory.
New distributed programming can effectively compute Lithum in normal super computer.
v9.0 has been tested extensively and the code is much more readable.
v9.1 has cut the pork and now can easily allocate my systems of choice.
v9.2 has implemented HDF5 because I had a huge IO issue.
v9.3 has sped up and or avoided various slow procedures.

See (Count Down) on WIKI.

Please cite these two papers until a proper writeup of Andromeda is published.

Jerke, Jonathan and Poirier Bill. "Two-Body Schr√∂dinger Wave Functions in a Plane-Wave Basis Via Separation of Dimensions." The Journal of Chemical Physics 148, no. 10 (2018): 104101.
Jerke, Jonathan, Jacek Karwowski, and Bill Poirier. "Exact Matrix Elements for General Two-Body Central-Force Interactions, Expressed as Sums of Products." Molecular Physics  (2018): 1-12.

